- ... my performance!
- Eh?!

32
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:03,630
This is it!
Good luck for the race!

33
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:08,469
Apparently you've gained his trust!

34
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:11,915
Though I'm not so optimistic.

35
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:15,200
Kishida has just arrived at the hospital.

36
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:17,357
He has bruises all over the body,

37
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:20,512
and he broke an arm and some ribs.

38
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:23,389
- It's all because of Haitani!
- Now ...

39
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:26,950
.. he has to stay in the
hospital for at least two months!

40
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:30,635
Frankly, I can't even
believe this has happened!

41
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:32,950
It's hard to
resist provocations.

42
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:38,553
Gunma, you know,
we said that the qualifications ...

43
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:41,154
...you got were great,
and if you continue...

44
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:44,073
...you should have a
good chance of winning!

45
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:50,355
It would be great if you
could beat the other competitors!

46
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:54,798
Quiet! He finished only
second-last on the track!

47
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:58,156
